@NODE Intro "Introduction"

A Short Introduction
--------------------

AMWAYDeck   is  a  DataBase  for  use  on  the  AMIGA  computer  by  AMWAY
Distributors.  I  designed  it to keep track of my ®AMWAY customers, their
orders and stock.

Created with ®CanDo3.8 on an accelerated Amiga 1200 with 18 megs of RAM.

I hope it works OK on your system. Please let @{"me" LINK Address} know if it doesn't.

@ENDNODE
@NODE SysReq "System Requirements"

  System requirements:
  --------------------

      Amiga 1200+

      The @{"CanDo libraries" LINK Install} in your LIBS: directory.

      Some RAM.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Install "Installation"

Installing AMWAYDeck
--------------------

To  install  AMWAYDeck  just  click  on  the  install  icon and follow the
instructions.

If  you  want  to  install it by hand, just copy the drawer "AMWAYDeck" to
your hard drive.

Some  of the programs like "AMWAYDeckV5.0" will need "DeckRunner" in order
for them to run.

Copy  the  "AMWAYDeck:C/DeckBrowser"  &  "AMWAYDeck:C/DeckRunner" files to
your C: directory.

You also need these Libraries to make it work:

         Cando.library : (Supplied in the Archive)

      Lowlevel.library : (Supplied in the Archive)

      Candogfx.library : (Supplied in the Archive)
                         Not necessary for this program but may be used in
                         other programs from this author.

Copy these libraries to your "Libs:" directory.

Well, that's it.

@ENDNODE
@NODE MainProg "Main Program"

Main Program Functions
----------------------

There are few things that the program does when it first starts up.

The first thing it does is to assign AMWAYDeck: to the Current Directory.
(No more messing about with assigns).

PS: Once you @{"Quit" LINK Quit} the program, the assign will be removed.

The next thing it does is look for the "AMWAYPrefs" file.

If  no "AMWAYPrefs" file is found then a "Prefences Program" will load up.
This is where you can set the "Preferences" of the program.

In  this  archive  I  have included my own defaults and information in the
drawers mentioned in the @{"Prefences Program" LINK Prefs}.

This  might  help  you  in  understanding  how  the program works and what
information to put in.

PLEASE NOTE: Because I hate requesters that come up with:

                       "Do you want to Quit?"

I have NOT put in this feature, so SAVE your work before quitting.

                          @{" Distributor Screen " LINK Dist}
                          @{" DataBase Screen    " LINK DB}
                          @{" Ordering Screen    " LINK Ord}
                          @{" Customer Screen    " LINK Cust}
                          @{" Tutorial           " LINK How}

@ENDNODE
@NODE Quit "Quitting the Program"

"QUIT"  HOTKEY = right Amiga + Q

When  you  select  the  "Close  Window"  button  or the "Quit" button, the
program deletes all the temp files in "RAM:" and quits.

As mentioned in the @{"Main Program" LINK MainProg},  I've NOT put in a safety feature with a
requester asking you if you want to quit.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Prefs "Preferences"

Setting your Preferences
------------------------

In  this  screen you can set your own "Directories" to save your files to,
plus you can set a Default Currency to use. IE: "$" or "Ł"

                     @{" Distributor Directory " LINK PrefsDist}
                     @{" DataBase Directory    " LINK PrefsData}
                     @{" Ordering Directory    " LINK PrefsOrd}
                     @{" Customer Directory    " LINK PrefsCust}

                     @{" Currency " LINK PrefsCurr}

                     @{" Menu " LINK PrefsMenu}

                     @{" Background Picture " LINK PrefsBGPic} NEW feature

If  no  Prefs  are set by you, then the "Default Settings" will be used by
the program. When the program starts it creates a directory in RAM: called
"AMWAYData"

It is in this drawer that most of the program files are saved.

The program creates four sub drawers in "RAM:AMWAYData" and they are:

                               CustData
                               DistData
                               OrderData
                               PrintData

If  you  haven't set your own Prefs, then these Drawers will be created on
your  system  as well, all except the "PrintData" dir. This drawer is used
to  store  temporary  print information that can be sent to the printer at
any time.

I  used  "RAM:"  as temporary storage, for speed, and for programming test
purposes.

         .---------.
         | WARNING |
         |         `-----------------------------------------------.
         |                                                         |
         | You must have this prefs program in order to create the |
         | AMWAYPREFS file. This file is crucial to the running of |
         | the rest of the program.                                |
         |                                                         |
         `---------------------------------------------------------'

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsDist "Distributor Directory"

Setting the path of the Distributor Directory
---------------------------------------------

To  the right of this field is a "Drawer" Button. Press this button to set
the directory that you want to save your data to. Once you have done this,
the  full  path  of  the  directory  will  be  typed  into the Distributor
Directory field.

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsData "DataBase Directory"

Setting the path of the DataBase Directory
------------------------------------------

To  the right of this field is a "Drawer" Button. Press this button to set
the directory that you want to save your data to. Once you have done this,
the  full  path of the directory will be typed into the DataBase Directory
field.

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsOrd "Ordering Directory"

Setting the path of the Ordering Directory
------------------------------------------

To  the right of this field is a "Drawer" Button. Press this button to set
the directory that you want to save your data to. Once you have done this,
the  full  path of the directory will be typed into the Ordering Directory
field.

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsCust "Customer Directory"

Setting the path of the Customer Directory
------------------------------------------

To  the right of this field is a "Drawer" Button. Press this button to set
the directory that you want to save your data to. Once you have done this,
the  full  path of the directory will be typed into the Customer Directory
field.

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsBGPic "Background Picture"

Having a BackGround  Picture for the screens in the Program
-----------------------------------------------------------

The  "BackGround  Picture"  field  has  a small Button to the right of it.
Press  on  this  button and a requester will appear. Select a picture that
you  would  like  as a background, the picture that you select will become
the default Background Picture. You will also see the picture displayed in
the  Preferences  Screen,  This  will  give  you  an  idea  as to what the
backround will look like.

Once you have selected the picture that you like, the "Background Picture"
field will have the path and file name of the picture that you selected in
it.

I have also added a NEW @{"Menu" LINK PrefsMenu} feature to the Prefs program.

NOTE:  To  create  your  own  pictures for your backgrounds, just run your
favorite Paint Program (DPaint, Personal Paint, Brilliance, Etc.)

Load  in  a  brush  and  fill  the  screen.  You  might  want  to load the
"Default.bg"  Picture  into  your  paint program, clear the screen, load a
brush  and  use brush remap to convert the colours. I used MWB colours for
my program, so you might try doing the above, to have the proper palette.

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsCurr "Currency"

Setting the Currency value
--------------------------

Press this cycle button to go through the different Curreny values, once
you have the currency for your country  selected,  press the @{"Save" LINK PrefsSave} button
to save the currency value to be used in the main program.

@ENDNODE
