@NODE PrefsLoad "Loading the Prefs File"

"Load"  MENU HOTKEY = right Amiga + L

This  Button or Menu option loads a file requester asking for the location
of  the  "AMWAYPrefs"  file. If no prefs file is selected then the Default
settings are used.

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsSave "Saving the Prefs File."

"Save" MENU HOTKEY = right Amiga + S

This Button or Menu option does an auto save of the file, AMWAYPrefs

                        to   "RAM:AMWAYData"
                    and to   "AMWAYDeck:AMWAYData"

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsQuit "To Quit Preferences."

"Quit" MENU HOTKEY = right Amiga + Q or the Close Gadget.

This  will quit the "Prefs" program, when it quits it does an auto save of
the "AMWAYPrefs" file to "RAM:AMWAYData"

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsDate "Date Format"

Setting the Date Format
-----------------------

           DD:MM:YY Day Month Year (Australia, Canada Etc)
           MM:DD:YY Month Day Year (USA, Europe Etc)

These are the two Date formats that you can select.

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsDistPic "Distributor Pic"

Selecting a "Distributor Pic" File
----------------------------------

This  menu  function  brings  up  a  requester  for  you  to  select which
Background Picture you would like to have in the "Distributor Screen"

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsDataPic "DataBase Pic"

Selecting a "DataBase Pic" File
-------------------------------

This  menu  function  brings  up  a  requester  for  you  to  select which
Background Picture you would like to have in the "DataBase Screen"

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsOrdPic "Ordering Pic"

Selecting a "Ordering Pic" File
-------------------------------

This  menu  function  brings  up  a  requester  for  you  to  select which
Background Picture you would like to have in the "Ordering Screen"

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsCustPic "Customer Pic"

Selecting a "Customer Pic" File
-------------------------------

This  menu  function  brings  up  a  requester  for  you  to  select which
Background Picture you would like to have in the "Customer Screen"

@ENDNODE
@NODE PrefsNoPic "No Background Picture."

Selecting "No Background Picture"
---------------------------------

This menu function will set the Default Backround Picture to "Nothing" and
clear  the  window.  Once this is done, no pictures will be seen in any of
the screens.

@ENDNODE
