@ENDNODE
@NODE DistName "Name Button & Field"

The Name Button & Field
-----------------------

Click on the Name button to clear the Name field.

The Name field is where you type in your Name.

NOTE:  Changing  your  name  in  "Name"  field will result in an automatic
change in the @{"Number" LINK "DistNumber"} and reset the Number to "0".

@ENDNODE
@NODE DistNumber "Number Button & Field"

The Number Button & Field
-------------------------

Click on the Number button to clear the Number field.

The Number field is where you type in your Number.

NOTE: If the "Number" is set to "0" the cursor stays in the "Number" field
or goes to the @{"Name" LINK DistName} field if that is also empty.

@ENDNODE
@NODE DistDate "Todays Date"

Todays Date
-----------

Click  on  this  button  to automatically set the current date and set the
@{"Order" LINK DistOrderNo} field to the correct order number.

If  when  you  first  start this program you have no settings, the Date is
automatically  set  to  the  current  Date. If you have settings saved the
program will load the date that was saved in the settings.

I  designed  this feature so you could see when you last used the program.
The  date  that is set in the "Distributor Screen" is used in the @{"customer" LINK Cust}
Receipt part of the program.

The  "Day,  Month,  Year  & Order Fields" are where you can enter your own
numbers.

@ENDNODE
@NODE DistInc " + & - "

+ & -

These buttons will increase or decrease the numbers in the "Day", "Month",
"Year" & "Order" fields.

Once  the  number in the field has reached its lowest or highest number it
resets the number to 1 or 0.

 EG: Once the number in the "Day" field reaches 32 and you click on "+"
     to increase the number, the number in the "Day" field returns to 1.

@ENDNODE
@NODE DistOrderNo "The Order Number"

The Order Number
----------------

This  button resets the number in the "Order" field. The "Order Number" is
calculated from the Date.

  EG: Week 1 is Order 1, Week 2 is Order 2 and so on.

@ENDNODE
@NODE DistNew "New"

"NEW"  HOTKEY = right Amiga + N

This  button  resets  all the fields in the "Distributor Screen". Use this
button If you want to start from scratch.

@ENDNODE
@NODE DistSponsor "Your Sponsor"

"SPONSOR"

This is where you enter your Sponsors Name and Number.

It functions as in the @{"Name" LINK DistName} & @{"Number" LINK DistNumber} buttons.

In order to be an "AMWAY" distributor you need to have a "Sponsor". If you
like, I could help you by becoming your "Sponsor". Just send me a reply to
my @{"Address" LINK "Address"}.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Load "Loading the Information"

"LOAD"  HOTKEY = right Amiga + L

This  Button  or  Menu  option  loads  a  requested  file from the current
directory, the Requester has Pattern matching.

  EG. Pattern: #?.Data

This will display any files with the .data suffix after them.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Save "Saving your Data"

"SAVING YOUR DATA"

    HOTKEY (Save) = right Amiga + S     HOTKEY (Save As) = right Amiga + A

These  Button and Menu options save the data to "RAM:" and to your current
directory in your hard drive.

The Save As option in the menu brings up a requester so you can enter your
own information.

When  Saving  your data in the "Ordering" & "Customer" screens the Data is
saved in this format:

          "Order-[23-01-97].Data"  or  "Order-[01-23-97].Data"
     "CustOrder-4[23-01-97].Data"  or  "CustOrder-4[01-23-97].Data"

This will help keep track of the day you ordered the products.

@ENDNODE
@NODE DistOpenData "Open DataBase"

Open DataBase
-------------

This Button or Menu option takes you to the Very Heart of the Program

               Drum roll please... The @{"DataBase" LINK DB}.

@ENDNODE
